{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633344","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633344"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17475"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17475","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17475"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0,0.14,0.48,0.33]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10165"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70744"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10165","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10165"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17475"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56210"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5453"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23766"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23791"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70744","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70744"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELife expectancy is a key population health indicator used to compare health outcomes between different populations and track changes over time.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes how period life expectancy is calculated?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Measures median survival time in longitudinal studies","Tracks actual survival of individuals born in the same year","Projects future mortality improvements for current population","Uses mortality rates from a specific time period applied to a hypothetical cohort","Averages age at death for all deaths in current year"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeriod life expectancy uses mortality rates from a specific time period applied to a hypothetical cohort\u003C/strong\u003E to estimate average lifespan. It assumes current mortality rates remain constant throughout life, providing a snapshot of mortality conditions at a particular time.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeasuring median survival time in longitudinal studies\u003C/strong\u003E describes a different epidemiological technique that follows individuals over time to determine survival patterns.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETracking actual survival of individuals born in the same year\u003C/strong\u003E refers to cohort life expectancy, which requires following real birth cohorts throughout their entire lifespan.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProjecting future mortality improvements for current population\u003C/strong\u003E is a method used in cohort life expectancy calculations that accounts for anticipated changes in mortality rates.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAveraging age at death for all deaths in current year\u003C/strong\u003E would produce misleading results as it fails to account for the population\u0027s age structure and would be heavily influenced by historical events.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPeriod life expectancy is widely used because it can be calculated using current data without needing to make assumptions about future mortality trends. However, it tends to underestimate actual life expectancy in populations where mortality rates are improving over time.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Life expectancy is the average number of years a person is expected to live from a given age, typically calculated from birth.","Period life expectancy uses current mortality rates while cohort life expectancy considers projected future changes in mortality.","Life expectancy calculations are fundamental to public health planning and policy development."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56210"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17475"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56210","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56210"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:38:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:40:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10165"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70744"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":nul